We need to parse the record. It says:

"BMI at baseline and at end of 15 months for Risperidone LAI and oral AAP groups;
Number of participants with Hyperlipidemia as determined by safety labs;
Number of participants with hyperglycemia based on safety labs;"

So markers: BMI (body mass index) at baseline and end of 15 months. Also hyperlipidemia count, hyperglycemia count. These are markers. We should list them as markers array with format "ACRONYM: expanded form". For BMI, acronym is BMI: Body Mass Index. For hyperlipidemia, maybe "Hyperlipidemia: Elevated lipid levels" but no acronym. Use "HLIP" maybe? But rule: If no acronym exists, create a logical abbreviation or use the shortest recognizable form. So we can use "HLIP" or "Hyperlipidemia". Let's choose "HLIP: Hyperlipidemia". For hyperglycemia, "HGlyc" or "Hyperglycemia". Use "HGlyc: Hyperglycemia".

Also mention counts: "Number of participants with Hyperlipidemia" etc. But markers are the condition itself. So list those.

Thus output JSON:

{
"analysis":"The record reports anthropometric and metabolic laboratory markers: body mass index measured at baseline and after 15 months, plus counts of participants identified with hyperlipidemia and hyperglycemia from safety lab results.",
"markers":[
"BMI: Body Mass Index",
"HLIP: Hyperlipidemia",
"HGlyc: Hyperglycemia"
]
}

Check formatting: Must be exactly one JSON object, keys analysis and markers. Ensure no trailing commas. Provide as plain JSON.
